,"body":"The Chaquopy build tool does produce wheels – we currently host them [here](https://chaquo.com/pypi-13.1/), and the Chaquopy Gradle plugin (either directly or via Briefcase) can build them into Android apps with a slightly patched version of pip. The equivalent for iOS is [this tool](https://github.com/beeware/mobile-forge) and [this repository](https://anaconda.org/beeware/repo).

Now that Android and iOS are officially supported in Python itself, we're planning to contribute support for these platforms to more general packaging tools such as cibuildwheel. The plan is that these mobile-specific packaging tools and repositories will eventually become obsolete, and projects will be able to build Android and iOS wheels with their existing workflows, and publish them on PyPI along with all the other platforms.

Testing on Android and iOS emulators is also possible on GitHub Actions, and we're already doing it in the Toga project. To see what this looks like, open [one of our recent CI runs](https://github.com/beeware/toga/actions/workflows/ci.yml?query=branch%3Amain) and look at the "testbed" jobs.

